scribus-ng (1.5.2+dfsg-4) experimental; urgency=medium

  * d/copyright: bump the year for debian/*.
  * d/patches:
    + (finally) drop qreal_double patch: scribus-ng builds fine everywhere now.
    + fix_FTBFS_BE: mark as upstreamed.
    + install-icons.patch: new patch from upstream trunk, to install the high
      resolution icons.
  * d/scribus-ng.data: stop installing manually the icons, and let the build
    system do it.
  * d/rules: add comments link to the upstream bugs we are workarounding.
  * d/watch: fixup dversionmangle rule.
    While on it, rewrite it all using a more modern format with version=4.

 -- Mattia Rizzolo <mattia@debian.org>  Mon, 15 May 2017 14:17:47 +0200

scribus-ng (1.5.2+dfsg-3) experimental; urgency=medium

  * d/p/series: sort according to their upstream status.
  * d/patches:
    + New patches backported from upstream trunk:
      - appdatadir: update appstream file and install location
      - upstream_14256-14257: drops mimelnk file, improve .desktop file,
        install .desktop.  This obsoletes the patch 'desktop.patch' (removed).
      - dynamic-freedesktop: dynamically generate scribus.desktop and
        scribus.appdata.xml and name them after -DCUSTOM-VERSIONTAG.
      - name-manpages-after-versiontag: rename the manpages after
        -DCUSTOM_VERSIONTAG
    + New patch not yet upstreamed:
      - fix_FTBFS_BE: fix FTBFS on big endian architectures.  This requires a
        new build dependency on extra-cmake-modules.
    + New non-upstreamable patch:
      - ng.patch: name the program 'Scribus NG' in the .desktop file.
  * Do not Build-Depend on libopenscenegraph-dev on arm*, to work around
    FTBFS on those architectures.

 -- Mattia Rizzolo <mattia@debian.org>  Wed, 01 Mar 2017 20:51:59 +0100

